LCP - Largest contentfull paint

LCP, or Largest Contentful Paint, is a metric that measures the time it takes for the largest content element on a web page to be rendered. It's crucial for user experience and SEO, indicating how quickly users can see meaningful content. Factors like server response times and render-blocking resources affect LCP. To optimize, focus on image and resource loading, and use tools like Lighthouse for measurement

and how fast your largest content loads defines your LCP score

improve -
make sure your first load image is not lazy loaded, use CDN for load images, use NEXT Image

